  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Requires catheterization &gt;24h hours following incontinence or pelvic reconstructive
             surgery

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Receipt of antibiotics for either prophylaxis or treatment of a known infection
             during the postoperative hospitalization

          -  Allergy to sulfonamides or trimethoprim

          -  Non-English speaking

          -  Pregnancy

          -  Breast feeding

          -  Severe renal impairment (creatinine clearance &lt;30)

          -  Patients taking dofetilide, methenamine, procaine, warfarin, procainamide,
             methotrexate.
      </textblock>
